---
const scenarios = [
  {
    label: "Broken board-prep cycle",
    cost: "8 to 12 hours per quarter across CEO, CFO, and General Counsel, at an internal billing rate of $500 to $1,500 per hour.",
    annual: "$16,000 to $72,000",
    detail: "of executive time, recovered when the cadence runs on rails instead of scrambling the week before.",
  },
  {
    label: "Ad-hoc earnings coordination",
    cost: "One quarter of script revisions, stakeholder chasing, and external IR back-and-forth typically consumes 20 to 40 hours of CFO and CEO time.",
    annual: "$40,000 to $240,000",
    detail: "across four quarters. A rebuilt cadence means your C-suite spends that time on the story, not the logistics.",
  },
  {
    label: "First-EA hire done wrong",
    cost: "A mis-hire in a senior EA role costs 6 to 9 months of salary ($60K to $125K+) plus the opportunity cost of leadership's unsupported calendar.",
    annual: "$75,000 to $200,000+",
    detail: "in direct and indirect cost. Done right, the EA function is force multiplier. Done wrong, it's a tax on the exec team.",
  },
];
---

<section class="bg-paper-deep py-16 md:py-20">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mb-12 md:mb-16" data-reveal>
      <p class="small-caps text-copper mb-4">The math</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink leading-[0.95] mb-6">
        What it <span class="italic font-display-italic">actually costs</span> to not fix this.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-soft text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Fractional EA work feels like an expense until you price what the current state is already costing you. Three honest calculations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-px bg-rule border border-rule" data-reveal>
      {scenarios.map((s, idx) => (
        <div class="bg-paper-deep grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-6 md:gap-10 px-6 md:px-8 py-7 md:py-9">
          <div class="md:col-span-1 flex items-start">
            <span class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-copper leading-none tabular">0{idx + 1}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-5">
            <p class="small-caps text-ink-muted mb-2">Scenario</p>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ink leading-tight mb-3">{s.label}</h3>
            <p class="text-ink-soft text-sm leading-relaxed">{s.cost}</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-6 md:border-l md:border-rule md:pl-8">
            <p class="small-caps text-copper mb-2">Annual exposure</p>
            <p class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-copper leading-none tabular mb-3">{s.annual}</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft text-sm leading-relaxed">{s.detail}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Closing reframe -->
    <div class="mt-10 md:mt-12 max-w-3xl" data-reveal>
      <p class="font-display-italic text-xl md:text-2xl text-ink leading-relaxed">
        Against those numbers, a $5,000 to $15,000 fractional engagement doesn't look like an expense. It looks like recovery of capital you're already spending, just not on anything that compounds.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
